## Quick Path

If you already have a normal Game Boy Camera save backup:

```bash
# 1. Check size. Normal Game Boy Camera SRAM is 128 KiB.
stat -c '%n %s bytes' GAMEBOYCAMERA.sav
# Expected: 131072 bytes, also written as 0x20000.

# 2. Extract all pictures with FlashGBX.
FlashGBX --cli --mode dmg --action gbcamera-extract \
  --gbcamera-palette grayscale \
  --gbcamera-outfile-format png \
  GAMEBOYCAMERA.sav

# 3. Output appears next to the save in a folder named after the save file.
# Example:
# ./GAMEBOYCAMERA/IMG_PC01.png
# ...
# ./GAMEBOYCAMERA/IMG_PC32.png
```

FlashGBX exports 32 images:

| File | Meaning |
|---|---|
| `IMG_PC01.png` ... `IMG_PC30.png` | Album photos in displayed album order |
| `IMG_PC31.png` | Game Face |
| `IMG_PC32.png` | Last Seen Image |

