## Dumping the Save from the Cartridge

If you still need to dump the save from a physical Game Boy Camera cartridge, use FlashGBX's save-backup action.

First try auto-detection:

```bash
FlashGBX --cli --mode dmg --action backup-save ./dumps/
```

If auto-detection fails, force the Game Boy Camera mapper and 128 KiB SRAM size:

```bash
FlashGBX --cli --mode dmg --action backup-save \
  --dmg-mbc 0xFC \
  --dmg-savetype 1m \
  --overwrite \
  ./dumps/GAMEBOYCAMERA.sav
```

Relevant constants:

| Concept | Value |
|---|---:|
| Game Boy mode | `dmg` |
| Game Boy Camera mapper | `0xFC` / `MAC-GBD+SRAM+BATTERY` |
| Normal save size | `0x20000` bytes / `131072` bytes / `128 KiB` |
| FlashGBX save-type label | `1m` |

After the dump:

```bash
stat -c '%s bytes' ./dumps/GAMEBOYCAMERA.sav
# Expected: 131072 bytes
```

