FlashGBX supports these palette names:

| CLI value | Meaning |
|---|---|
| `grayscale` | Neutral white-to-black grayscale |
| `dmg` | Original Game Boy-style green palette |
| `sgb` | Super Game Boy-style palette |
| `cgb1` | Game Boy Color / Pocket Camera-style palette |
| `cgb2` | Game Boy Camera Gold-style palette |
| `cgb3` | Game Boy Camera USA/EUR-style palette |

Example:

```bash
FlashGBX --cli --action gbcamera-extract \
  --gbcamera-palette dmg \
  --gbcamera-outfile-format png \
  GAMEBOYCAMERA.sav
```

### Other output formats

```bash
FlashGBX --cli --action gbcamera-extract --gbcamera-outfile-format png GAMEBOYCAMERA.sav
FlashGBX --cli --action gbcamera-extract --gbcamera-outfile-format bmp GAMEBOYCAMERA.sav
