## Savegame Layout

The save does not contain raw camera sensor values. It contains already-processed Game Boy tile graphics: 2 bits per pixel, arranged as normal 8x8 tiles.

| Area | Offset | Size / stride | Meaning |
|---|---:|---:|---|
| Full normal save | `0x00000` | `0x20000` / 128 KiB | Normal Game Boy Camera SRAM backup |
| Last Seen Image | `0x00000` | `0x1000` | Last captured image buffer |
| Album order table | `0x011D7` | 30 bytes | Maps displayed album order to physical slots |
| Game Face | `0x011FC` | `0x1000` | Special face image used by the camera software |
| Album photos | `0x02000 + slot * 0x1000` | `0x1000` stride each | 30 physical album slots |

### Image dimensions

| Image kind | Tile dimensions | Pixel dimensions in FlashGBX |
|---|---:|---:|
| Normal album photo | `16 x 14` tiles | `128 x 112` |
| Game Face | `16 x 14` tiles | `128 x 112` |
| Last Seen Image | `16 x 16` tiles, cropped | `128 x 123` |

A normal photo block has a `0x1000` byte stride, but the visible `128 x 112` image consumes only:

```text
16 tile columns * 14 tile rows * 16 bytes per tile = 3584 bytes = 0x0E00
```

So do not assume every byte in the `0x1000` block becomes visible pixel data.

