## Validation and Troubleshooting

| Symptom | Likely cause | Fix |
|---|---|---|
| `Couldn't parse the save data file.` | File is not 128 KiB, or it is a 1 MiB Photo! directory dump. | Check size. For 1 MiB, slice one `0x20000` roll first. |
| Images are blank | Empty save slots, wrong file, or bad dump. | Check manifest, redump, try GUI thumbnails. |
| Images look like garbage | Wrong save type, offset bug, or bad 2bpp decode bit order. | Verify offsets and tile bitplane formula. |
| All photos look shifted | Tile traversal wrong. | Use row-major tile order: `tile_y`, then `tile_x`. |
| Black/white inverted | Palette index mapping wrong. | FlashGBX uses `(second_bit << 1) | first_bit`; index `0` is lightest. |
| Deleted images still export | Expected. Old pixel data may still exist until overwritten. | Mark them in metadata or hide them in UI. |
| CLI cannot extract 1 MiB Photo! dump | CLI expects 128 KiB for `PocketCamera.LoadFile(path)`. | Slice the 1 MiB file or use the GUI. |
| JPG looks bad | JPEG is lossy. | Use PNG. |
| Backup from hardware fails | Dirty contacts, wrong mode, USB permissions, firmware issue. | Use `--mode dmg`, clean contacts, update firmware, check serial permissions. |

