## Implementation Checklist

For your own implementation, the minimum viable extractor is:

- [ ] Read `.sav` bytes.
- [ ] Accept `0x20000`; optionally accept `0x100000` with roll selection.
- [ ] Parse album order at `0x11D7`.
- [ ] For 30 album photos, use `0x2000 + physical_slot * 0x1000`.
- [ ] Decode each photo as 16 x 14 Game Boy 2bpp tiles.
- [ ] Decode Game Face from `0x11FC` as 16 x 14 tiles.
- [ ] Decode Last Seen from `0x0000` as 16 x 16 tiles, crop to 128 x 123 if you want FlashGBX-compatible output.
- [ ] Convert palette indices to RGBA.
- [ ] Export PNG or pass RGBA to your UI.
- [ ] Preserve metadata: display index, physical slot, offset, deleted, empty.

